        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">Down, | Beckenham, Kent.</hi></placeName>
                    <date>Jan. 18<hi rend="superscript">th</hi></date>
                    <salute>My dear Paget</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>Very many thanks for your note.<ref target="#foot.f2"/> One is led at once to suspect reversion, though that is an easy &amp; tempting to trap to fall into. Your sketch has called up a fairly vivid recollection in my mind of a gentleman (M.P. for Shropshire) with whom I used as a boy often to shoot, &amp; who had ears such as you describe.—<ref target="#foot.f3"/> I must look to the ears of our brethren in the Zool. Gardens.—</p>
<p>Yours very sincerely | Ch Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>
            <div type="tnotes">
                <note xml:id="tnote.n1">1.3 in my mind] <hi rend="italic">interl</hi> </note>
                <note xml:id="tnote.n2">1.3 as a boy 1.4] <hi rend="italic">interl</hi> </note>
            </div>

            
            
            
            
            
            
